14 February 2016On Tuesday, 16 February at 10:00am, Social Protection, Community and Human Development cluster chaired by Minister Bathabile Dlamini will hold a media briefing on the implementation of the Government Programme of Action for the post State of the Nation Address 2016. The briefing will be held at Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town with a link up to Tshedimosetso House (GCIS), Pretoria.On Wednesday, 17 February at 09:00am, Economic Sector, Employment and Infrastructure development cluster chaired by Minister Gugile Nkwinti will hold a media briefing on the implementation of the Government Programme of Action for the post State of the Nation Address 2016. The briefing will be held at Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town with a link up to Tshedimosetso House (GCIS), Pretoria. (postponed until further notice) On Thursday, 18 February at 10h00, The Minister in the Presidency for Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation, Jeff Radebe will address media on the outcome of the Cabinet meeting to be held on Wednesday, 17 February 2016. Full details will be communicated through a media advisory during the week.On Sunday, 21 February at 09:00am, Justice, Crime Prevention and Security Cluster chaired by Minister of Defence and Military Veterans, Nosiviwe Mapisa- Nqakula will hold a media briefing on the implementation of the Government Programme of Action for the post State of the Nation Address 2016. The briefing will be held at Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town with a link up to Tshedimosetso House (GCIS), Pretoria. (postponed until further notice) In addition to these media briefings, Ministers participate in various public events. For a comprehensive list of national and provincial government activities visit www.gov.za. Should there be changes in the information above, members of the media will be notified accordingly.Enquiries: Themba Sepotokele Cell: 082 490 9869Issued by Government Communication and Information System